last_episode_to_air.name: Best Summer Ever!
last_episode_to_air.overview: As summer draws to a close, campers participate in a Wazi-wide dodge ball game. The campers dress up for a fancy banquet before saying their goodbyes and heading back home.

name: Bug Juice: My Adventures at Camp
original_name: Bug Juice: My Adventures at Camp
overview: Return to Camp Waziyatah for a contemporary new installment of the unscripted docu-series capturing the authentic adventures of a group of kids age 10-12 as they head to summer camp, join in exciting and challenging outdoor activities, establish tight bonds with bunkmates and create unforgettable memories.

episodes.name: Wazi, Wazi, Waziyatah!
episodes.overview: It's arrival day at Camp Waziyatah, and as campers say goodbye to their families, most of the kids take to camp like ducks to water, but some newcomers have a harder time.

episodes.name: The S'more the Better
episodes.overview: The girls of Pines 4 eagerly await the arrival of two new cabin mates as the boys of Pines 9 help Darryl bounce back after a disappointing swim test.

episodes.name: TJ vs. The Blob
episodes.overview: The 4th of July at Wazi has the kids excited to take on new challenges. Vegas night tests friendships when Brynn decides to take a risk, dividing the cabin and testing friendships.

episodes.name: Tacos for Breakfast
episodes.overview: The cabins have new counselors and the kids feast on tacos for breakfast. At the evening event, the kids have their fortunes read and the counselors are soaked in a dunk tank.

episodes.name: Friendship vs. Zombies
episodes.overview: There's a zombie breakout and the power of friendship is the only defense! The campers are tested in an epic game of tag. An underground candy trade has the camp buzzing.

episodes.name: Gettin' Sketch-y
episodes.overview: Tensions run high for the girls of Pines 4 after sleeping arrangements at the campout divides the girls. The boys' and girls' cabins prep comedy sketches for Wazi skit night.

episodes.name: It's On!
episodes.overview: Color War breaks the whole camp into 4 teams for an epic, 2 day, non-stop competition. Everyone works hard for the win but only one team will stand victorious.

episodes.name: Later, Taters!
episodes.overview: The girls celebrate the end of Session 1 with a rolling competition, while some of the boys tackle their fears at the waterfront. All of Wazi comes together for a special campfire.

episodes.name: Fishing for Friends
episodes.overview: Fun cabin-bonding activities kicks off the start of session two as new campers meet their counselors and cabin mates. The remaining first session kids navigate a new cabin dynamic.

episodes.name: Everyday I'm Paddlin'
episodes.overview: Damian's leadership lands him in cold water. Both cabins turn counselors into Superheroes, with limited resources and lots of imagination.

episodes.name: Taco of Terror
episodes.overview: It's camp fear(less) at Wazi. Lucy faces a 50ft climbing wall, blindfolded and one legged. A taco of terror scares no one and Halloween in summer is a night of fright.

episodes.name: Try, Try (Try) Again
episodes.overview: Andrew gets Doggy, Izzy gets Hare-y and Aaralyn gets grape-y for the final play of summer. The Untalent show highlights the bizarre talents of campers.

episodes.name: Fables and Tables
episodes.overview: Wazi Casino opens its doors for card games and weddings, with Leo getting nicknamed the wedding bandit. Alex and Andrew take to the lake to reach their goals.

episodes.name: Challenge Makers, Ankle Breakers and Breakout Fakers
episodes.overview: Challenges are on at Wazi! Grace discovers that camp can still be fun, even on crutches. Tug of War and Jigs are the theme of the night for Scottish Highland Games.

episodes.name: The Quest for the Cup
episodes.overview: Parker Cup, an epic 2-day competition, divides camp and tests friendships. Kids battle it out in a camp-wide relay race, a sky-high egg-drop and a penalty kick round of soccer.

episodes.name: Best Summer Ever!
episodes.overview: As summer draws to a close, campers participate in a Wazi-wide dodge ball game. The campers dress up for a fancy banquet before saying their goodbyes and heading back home.
